#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="dn5"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "dn5:0.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Long Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn5:0.2"
msgid "Kūṭadantasutta "
msgstr "With Kūṭadanta "

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "dn5:0.3"
msgid "1. Khāṇumatakabrāhmaṇagahapatikā "
msgstr "1. The Brahmins and Householders of Khāṇumata "

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts-cs1, pts-vp-pli1.127, sc1
msgctxt "dn5:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "dn5:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā magadhesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi yena khāṇumataṃ nāma magadhānaṃ brāhmaṇagāmo tadavasari. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Magadhans together with a large Saṅgha of around five hundred mendicants when he arrived at a village of the Magadhan brahmins named Khāṇumata. "

# NOTE: RD has “pleasaunce”, MW has “park” but the text has nothing.
msgctxt "dn5:1.3"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā khāṇumate viharati ambalaṭṭhikāyaṃ. "
msgstr "There he stayed nearby at Ambalaṭṭhikā. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:1.4"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena kūṭadanto brāhmaṇo khāṇumataṃ ajjhāvasati sattussadaṃ satiṇakaṭṭhodakaṃ sadhaññaṃ rājabhoggaṃ raññā māgadhena seniyena bimbisārena dinnaṃ rājadāyaṃ brahmadeyyaṃ. "
msgstr "Now at that time the brahmin Kūṭadanta was living in Khāṇumata. It was a crown property given by King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha, teeming with living creatures, full of hay, wood, water, and grain, a royal endowment of the highest quality. "

msgctxt "dn5:1.5"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena kūṭadantassa brāhmaṇassa mahāyañño upakkhaṭo hoti. "
msgstr "Now at that time Kūṭadanta had prepared a great sacrifice. "

msgctxt "dn5:1.6"
msgid "Satta ca usabhasatāni satta ca vacchatarasatāni satta ca vacchatarīsatāni satta ca ajasatāni satta ca urabbhasatāni thūṇūpanītāni honti yaññatthāya. "
msgstr "Bulls, bullocks, heifers, goats and rams—seven hundred of each—had been led to the post for the sacrifice. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2, pts-vp-pli1.128, sc2
msgctxt "dn5:2.1"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho khāṇumatakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā: "
msgstr "The brahmins and householders of Khāṇumataka heard: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:2.2"
msgid "“samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito magadhesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi khāṇumataṃ anuppatto khāṇumate viharati ambalaṭṭhikāyaṃ. "
msgstr "“It seems the ascetic Gotama—a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family—has arrived at Khāṇumataka and is staying in a forest nearby. "

msgctxt "dn5:2.3"
msgid "Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato: "
msgstr "He has this good reputation: "

msgctxt "dn5:2.4"
msgid "‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti. "
msgstr "‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’ "

msgctxt "dn5:2.5"
msgid "So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti. "
msgstr "He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others. "

msgctxt "dn5:2.6"
msgid "So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti. "
msgstr "He teaches Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. "

msgctxt "dn5:2.7"
msgid "Sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti. "
msgstr "It’s good to see such perfected ones.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "dn5:2.8"
msgid "Atha kho khāṇumatakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā khāṇumatā nikkhamitvā saṅghasaṅghī gaṇībhūtā yena ambalaṭṭhikā tenupasaṅkamanti. "
msgstr "Then, having departed Khāṇumataka, they formed into companies and headed to Ambalaṭṭhikā. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3, sc4
msgctxt "dn5:3.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena kūṭadanto brāhmaṇo uparipāsāde divāseyyaṃ upagato hoti. "
msgstr "Now at that time the brahmin Kūṭadanta had retired to the upper floor of his stilt longhouse for his midday nap. "

msgctxt "dn5:3.2"
msgid "Addasā kho kūṭadanto brāhmaṇo khāṇumatake brāhmaṇagahapatike khāṇumatā nikkhamitvā saṅghasaṅghī gaṇībhūte yena ambalaṭṭhikā tenupasaṅkamante. "
msgstr "He saw the brahmins and householders heading for Ambalaṭṭhikā, "

msgctxt "dn5:3.3"
msgid "Disvā khattaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "and addressed his steward, "

msgctxt "dn5:3.4"
msgid "“kiṃ nu kho, bho khatte, khāṇumatakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā khāṇumatā nikkhamitvā saṅghasaṅghī gaṇībhūtā yena ambalaṭṭhikā tenupasaṅkamantī”ti? "
msgstr "“My steward, why are the brahmins and householders headed for Ambalaṭṭhikā?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "dn5:3.5"
msgid "“Atthi kho, bho, samaṇo gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito magadhesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi khāṇumataṃ anuppatto, khāṇumate viharati ambalaṭṭhikāyaṃ. "
msgstr "“The ascetic Gotama has arrived at Khāṇumataka and is staying at Ambalaṭṭhikā. "

msgctxt "dn5:3.6"
msgid "Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato: "
msgstr "He has this good reputation: "

msgctxt "dn5:3.7"
msgid "‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti. "
msgstr "‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’ "

msgctxt "dn5:3.8"
msgid "Tamete bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamantī”ti. "
msgstr "They’re going to see that Master Gotama.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs4, pts-vp-pli1.129, sc6
msgctxt "dn5:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho kūṭadantassa brāhmaṇassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Kūṭadanta thought, "

msgctxt "dn5:4.2"
msgid "“sutaṃ kho pana metaṃ: "
msgstr "“I’ve heard that "

msgctxt "dn5:4.3"
msgid "‘samaṇo gotamo tividhaṃ yaññasampadaṃ soḷasaparikkhāraṃ jānātī’ti. "
msgstr "the ascetic Gotama knows how to accomplish the sacrifice with three modes and sixteen accessories. "

msgctxt "dn5:4.4"
msgid "Na kho panāhaṃ jānāmi tividhaṃ yaññasampadaṃ soḷasaparikkhāraṃ. "
msgstr "I don’t know about that, "

msgctxt "dn5:4.5"
msgid "Icchāmi cāhaṃ mahāyaññaṃ yajituṃ. "
msgstr "but I wish to perform a great sacrifice. "

msgctxt "dn5:4.6"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ upasaṅkamitvā tividhaṃ yaññasampadaṃ soḷasaparikkhāraṃ puccheyyan”ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I ask him how to accomplish the sacrifice with three modes and sixteen accessories?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "dn5:4.7"
msgid "Atha kho kūṭadanto brāhmaṇo khattaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then Kūṭadanta addressed his steward, "

msgctxt "dn5:4.8"
msgid "“tena hi, bho khatte, yena khāṇumatakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā tenupasaṅkama. upasaṅkamitvā khāṇumatake brāhmaṇagahapatike evaṃ vadehi: "
msgstr "“Well then, go to the brahmins and householders and say to them: "

msgctxt "dn5:4.9"
msgid "‘kūṭadanto, bho, brāhmaṇo evamāha—"
msgstr "‘Sirs, the brahmin Kūṭadanta asks "

msgctxt "dn5:4.10"
msgid "āgamentu kira bhavanto, kūṭadantopi brāhmaṇo samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissatī’”ti. "
msgstr "you to wait, as he will also go to see the ascetic Gotama.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:4.11"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho so khattā kūṭadantassa brāhmaṇassa paṭissutvā yena khāṇumatakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā tenupasaṅkami. upasaṅkamitvā khāṇumatake brāhmaṇagahapatike etadavoca: "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied the steward, and did as he was asked. "

msgctxt "dn5:4.12"
msgid "“kūṭadanto, bho, brāhmaṇo evamāha: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn5:4.13"
msgid "‘āgamentu kira bhonto, kūṭadantopi brāhmaṇo samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissatī’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn5:4.14"
msgid "2. Kūṭadantaguṇakathā "
msgstr "2. The Qualities of Kūṭadanta "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs5, sc8
msgctxt "dn5:5.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena anekāni brāhmaṇasatāni khāṇumate paṭivasanti: "
msgstr "Now at that time several hundred brahmins were residing in Khāṇumata "

msgctxt "dn5:5.2"
msgid "“kūṭadantassa brāhmaṇassa mahāyaññaṃ anubhavissāmā”ti. "
msgstr "thinking to participate in Kūṭadanta’s sacrifice. "

msgctxt "dn5:5.3"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho te brāhmaṇā: "
msgstr "They heard that "

msgctxt "dn5:5.4"
msgid "“kūṭadanto kira brāhmaṇo samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissatī”ti. "
msgstr "Kūṭadanta was going to see the ascetic Gotama. "

#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "dn5:5.5"
msgid "Atha kho te brāhmaṇā yena kūṭadanto brāhmaṇo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu. upasaṅkamitvā kūṭadantaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "They approached Kūṭadanta and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:5.6"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira bhavaṃ kūṭadanto samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Is it really true that you are going to see the ascetic Gotama?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:5.7"
msgid "“Evaṃ kho me, bho, hoti: "
msgstr "“Yes, gentlemen, it is true.” "

msgctxt "dn5:5.8"
msgid "‘ahampi samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissāmī’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs6, pts-vp-pli1.130, sc10
msgctxt "dn5:6.1"
msgid "“Mā bhavaṃ kūṭadanto samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkami. "
msgstr "“Please don’t! "

msgctxt "dn5:6.2"
msgid "Na arahati bhavaṃ kūṭadanto samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ. "
msgstr "It’s not appropriate for you to go to see the ascetic Gotama. "

msgctxt "dn5:6.3"
msgid "Sace bhavaṃ kūṭadanto samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissati, bhoto kūṭadantassa yaso hāyissati, samaṇassa gotamassa yaso abhivaḍḍhissati. "
msgstr "For if you do so, your reputation will diminish and his will increase. "

msgctxt "dn5:6.4"
msgid "Yampi bhoto kūṭadantassa yaso hāyissati, samaṇassa gotamassa yaso abhivaḍḍhissati, imināpaṅgena na arahati bhavaṃ kūṭadanto samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ. "
msgstr "For this reason it’s not appropriate for you to go to see the ascetic Gotama; "

msgctxt "dn5:6.5"
msgid "Samaṇo tveva gotamo arahati bhavantaṃ kūṭadantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ. "
msgstr "it’s appropriate that he comes to see you. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "dn5:6.6"
msgid "Bhavañhi kūṭadanto ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena. "
msgstr "You are well born on both your mother’s and father’s side, of pure descent, irrefutable and impeccable in questions of ancestry back to the seventh paternal generation. "

msgctxt "dn5:6.7"
msgid "Yampi bhavaṃ kūṭadanto ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena, imināpaṅgena na arahati bhavaṃ kūṭadanto samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ. "
msgstr "For this reason it’s not appropriate for you to go to see the ascetic Gotama; "

msgctxt "dn5:6.8"
msgid "Samaṇo tveva gotamo arahati bhavantaṃ kūṭadantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ. "
msgstr "it’s appropriate that he comes to see you. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "dn5:6.9"
msgid "Bhavañhi kūṭadanto aḍḍho mahaddhano mahābhogo pahūtavittūpakaraṇo pahūtajātarūparajato … pe … "
msgstr "You’re rich, affluent, and wealthy, with lots of property and assets, and lots of money and grain … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "dn5:6.10"
msgid "Bhavañhi kūṭadanto ajjhāyako mantadharo tiṇṇaṃ vedānaṃ pāragū sanighaṇḍukeṭubhānaṃ sākkharappabhedānaṃ itihāsapañcamānaṃ padako veyyākaraṇo lokāyatamahāpurisalakkhaṇesu anavayo … pe … "
msgstr "You recite and remember the hymns, and have mastered the three Vedas, together with their vocabularies, ritual, phonology and etymology, and the testament as fifth. You know philology and grammar, and are well versed in cosmology and the marks of a great man. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "dn5:6.11"
msgid "Bhavañhi kūṭadanto abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgato brahmavaṇṇī brahmavacchasī akhuddāvakāso dassanāya … pe … "
msgstr "You are attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty. You are magnificent, splendid, remarkable to behold. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "dn5:6.12"
msgid "Bhavañhi kūṭadanto sīlavā vuddhasīlī vuddhasīlena samannāgato … pe … "
msgstr "You are ethical, mature in ethical conduct. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "dn5:6.13"
msgid "Bhavañhi kūṭadanto kalyāṇavāco kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā … pe … "
msgstr "You’re a good speaker, with a polished, clear, and articulate voice that expresses the meaning. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "dn5:6.14"
msgid "Bhavañhi kūṭadanto bahūnaṃ ācariyapācariyo tīṇi māṇavakasatāni mante vāceti, bahū kho pana nānādisā nānājanapadā māṇavakā āgacchanti bhoto kūṭadantassa santike mantatthikā mante adhiyitukāmā … pe … "
msgstr "You teach the teachers of many, and teach three hundred students to recite the hymns. Many students come from various districts and countries for the sake of the hymns, wishing to learn the hymns. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "dn5:6.15"
msgid "Bhavañhi kūṭadanto jiṇṇo vuddho mahallako addhagato vayoanuppatto. "
msgstr "You’re old, elderly and senior, advanced in years, and have reached the final stage of life. "

msgctxt "dn5:6.16"
msgid "Samaṇo gotamo taruṇo ceva taruṇapabbajito ca … pe … "
msgstr "The ascetic Gotama is young, and has newly gone forth. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "dn5:6.17"
msgid "Bhavañhi kūṭadanto rañño māgadhassa seniyassa bimbisārassa sakkato garukato mānito pūjito apacito … pe … "
msgstr "You’re honored, respected, revered, venerated, and esteemed by King Bimbisāra of Magadha … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "dn5:6.18"
msgid "Bhavañhi kūṭadanto brāhmaṇassa pokkharasātissa sakkato garukato mānito pūjito apacito … pe … "
msgstr "and the brahmin Pokkharasāti. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.131, sc21
msgctxt "dn5:6.19"
msgid "Bhavañhi kūṭadanto khāṇumataṃ ajjhāvasati sattussadaṃ satiṇakaṭṭhodakaṃ sadhaññaṃ rājabhoggaṃ raññā māgadhena seniyena bimbisārena dinnaṃ rājadāyaṃ brahmadeyyaṃ. "
msgstr "You live in Khāṇumata, a crown property given by King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha, teeming with living creatures, full of hay, wood, water, and grain, a royal endowment of the highest quality. "

msgctxt "dn5:6.20"
msgid "Yampi bhavaṃ kūṭadanto khāṇumataṃ ajjhāvasati sattussadaṃ satiṇakaṭṭhodakaṃ sadhaññaṃ rājabhoggaṃ, raññā māgadhena seniyena bimbisārena dinnaṃ rājadāyaṃ brahmadeyyaṃ, imināpaṅgena na arahati bhavaṃ kūṭadanto samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ. "
msgstr "For this reason it’s not appropriate for you to go to see the ascetic Gotama; "

msgctxt "dn5:6.21"
msgid "Samaṇo tveva gotamo arahati bhavantaṃ kūṭadantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamitun”ti. "
msgstr "it’s appropriate that he comes to see you.” "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn5:6.22"
msgid "3. Buddhaguṇakathā "
msgstr "3. The Qualities of the Buddha "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs7, sc22
msgctxt "dn5:7.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, kūṭadanto brāhmaṇo te brāhmaṇe etadavoca: "
msgstr "When they had spoken, Kūṭadanta said to those brahmins: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc23
msgctxt "dn5:7.2"
msgid "“Tena hi, bho, mamapi suṇātha, yathā mayameva arahāma taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ, "
msgstr "“Well then, gentlemen, listen to why it’s appropriate for me to go to see the ascetic Gotama, "

msgctxt "dn5:7.3"
msgid "na tveva arahati so bhavaṃ gotamo amhākaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ. "
msgstr "and it’s not appropriate for him to come to see me. "

msgctxt "dn5:7.4"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena. "
msgstr "He is well born on both his mother’s and father’s side, of pure descent, irrefutable and impeccable in questions of ancestry back to the seventh paternal generation. "

msgctxt "dn5:7.5"
msgid "Yampi, bho, samaṇo gotamo ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena, imināpaṅgena na arahati so bhavaṃ gotamo amhākaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ. "
msgstr "For this reason it’s not appropriate for the ascetic Gotama to come to see me; "

msgctxt "dn5:7.6"
msgid "Atha kho mayameva arahāma taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ. "
msgstr "rather, it’s appropriate for me to go to see him. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc24
msgctxt "dn5:7.7"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo mahantaṃ ñātisaṅghaṃ ohāya pabbajito … pe … "
msgstr "When he went forth he abandoned a large family circle. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc25
msgctxt "dn5:7.8"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo pahūtaṃ hiraññasuvaṇṇaṃ ohāya pabbajito bhūmigatañca vehāsaṭṭhaṃ ca … pe … "
msgstr "When he went forth he abandoned abundant gold coin and bullion stored in dungeons and towers. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc26
msgctxt "dn5:7.9"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo daharova samāno yuvā susukāḷakeso bhadrena yobbanena samannāgato paṭhamena vayasā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito … pe … "
msgstr "He went forth from the lay life to homelessness while still a youth, young, black-haired, blessed with youth, in the prime of life. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc27
msgctxt "dn5:7.10"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo akāmakānaṃ mātāpitūnaṃ assumukhānaṃ rudantānaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito … pe … "
msgstr "Though his mother and father wished otherwise, weeping with tearful faces, he shaved off his hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and went forth from the lay life to homelessness. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.132, sc28
msgctxt "dn5:7.11"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgato brahmavaṇṇī brahmavacchasī akhuddāvakāso dassanāya … pe … "
msgstr "He is attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty. He is magnificent, splendid, remarkable to behold. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc29
msgctxt "dn5:7.12"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo sīlavā ariyasīlī kusalasīlī kusalasīlena samannāgato … pe … "
msgstr "He is ethical, possessing ethical conduct that is noble and skillful. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc30
msgctxt "dn5:7.13"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo kalyāṇavāco kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā … pe … "
msgstr "He’s a good speaker, with a polished, clear, and articulate voice that expresses the meaning. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc31
msgctxt "dn5:7.14"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo bahūnaṃ ācariyapācariyo … pe … "
msgstr "He’s a teacher of teachers. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc32
msgctxt "dn5:7.15"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo khīṇakāmarāgo vigatacāpallo … pe … "
msgstr "He has ended sensual desire, and is rid of caprice. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc33
msgctxt "dn5:7.16"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo kammavādī kiriyavādī apāpapurekkhāro brahmaññāya pajāya … pe … "
msgstr "He teaches the efficacy of deeds and action. He doesn’t wish any harm upon the community of brahmins. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc34
msgctxt "dn5:7.17"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo uccā kulā pabbajito asambhinnakhattiyakulā … pe … "
msgstr "He went forth from an eminent family of unbroken aristocratic lineage. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc35
msgctxt "dn5:7.18"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo aḍḍhā kulā pabbajito mahaddhanā mahābhogā … pe … "
msgstr "He went forth from a rich, affluent, and wealthy family. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc36
msgctxt "dn5:7.19"
msgid "Samaṇaṃ khalu, bho, gotamaṃ tiroraṭṭhā tirojanapadā pañhaṃ pucchituṃ āgacchanti … pe … "
msgstr "People come from distant lands and distant countries to question him. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc37
msgctxt "dn5:7.20"
msgid "Samaṇaṃ khalu, bho, gotamaṃ anekāni devatāsahassāni pāṇehi saraṇaṃ gatāni … pe … "
msgstr "Many thousands of deities have gone for refuge for life to him. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc38
msgctxt "dn5:7.21"
msgid "Samaṇaṃ khalu, bho, gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato: "
msgstr "He has this good reputation: "

msgctxt "dn5:7.22"
msgid "‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti … pe … "
msgstr "‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’ … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc39
msgctxt "dn5:7.23"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇehi samannāgato … pe … "
msgstr "He has the thirty-two marks of a great man. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc40
msgctxt "dn5:7.24"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo ehisvāgatavādī sakhilo sammodako abbhākuṭiko uttānamukho pubbabhāsī … pe … "
msgstr "He is welcoming, congenial, polite, smiling, open, the first to speak. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc41
msgctxt "dn5:7.25"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo catunnaṃ parisānaṃ sakkato garukato mānito pūjito apacito … pe … "
msgstr "He’s honored, respected, revered, venerated, and esteemed by the four assemblies. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc42
msgctxt "dn5:7.26"
msgid "Samaṇe khalu, bho, gotame bahū devā ca manussā ca abhippasannā … pe … "
msgstr "Many gods and humans are devoted to him. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc43
msgctxt "dn5:7.27"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo yasmiṃ gāme vā nigame vā paṭivasati na tasmiṃ gāme vā nigame vā amanussā manusse viheṭhenti … pe … "
msgstr "While he is residing in a village or town, non-human entities do not harass them. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc44
msgctxt "dn5:7.28"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo saṅghī gaṇī gaṇācariyo puthutitthakarānaṃ aggamakkhāyati, yathā kho pana, bho, etesaṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ yathā vā tathā vā yaso samudāgacchati, na hevaṃ samaṇassa gotamassa yaso samudāgato. "
msgstr "He leads an order and a community, and teaches a community, and is said to be the best of the various religious founders. He didn’t come by his fame in the same ways as those other ascetics and brahmins. "

msgctxt "dn5:7.29"
msgid "Atha kho anuttarāya vijjācaraṇasampadāya samaṇassa gotamassa yaso samudāgato … pe … "
msgstr "Rather, he came by his fame due to his supreme knowledge and conduct. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.133, sc45
msgctxt "dn5:7.30"
msgid "Samaṇaṃ khalu, bho, gotamaṃ rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro saputto sabhariyo sapariso sāmacco pāṇehi saraṇaṃ gato … pe … "
msgstr "King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha and his wives and children have gone for refuge for life to the ascetic Gotama. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc46
msgctxt "dn5:7.31"
msgid "Samaṇaṃ khalu, bho, gotamaṃ rājā pasenadi kosalo saputto sabhariyo sapariso sāmacco pāṇehi saraṇaṃ gato … pe … "
msgstr "King Pasenadi of Kosala and his wives and children have gone for refuge for life to the ascetic Gotama. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc47
msgctxt "dn5:7.32"
msgid "Samaṇaṃ khalu, bho, gotamaṃ brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti saputto sabhariyo sapariso sāmacco pāṇehi saraṇaṃ gato … pe … "
msgstr "The brahmin Pokkharasāti and his wives and children have gone for refuge for life to the ascetic Gotama. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc48
msgctxt "dn5:7.33"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo rañño māgadhassa seniyassa bimbisārassa sakkato garukato mānito pūjito apacito … pe … "
msgstr "He’s honored, respected, revered, venerated, and esteemed by King Bimbisāra of Magadha … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc49
msgctxt "dn5:7.34"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo rañño pasenadissa kosalassa sakkato garukato mānito pūjito apacito … pe … "
msgstr "King Pasenadi of Kosala … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc50
msgctxt "dn5:7.35"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo brāhmaṇassa pokkharasātissa sakkato garukato mānito pūjito apacito … pe … "
msgstr "and the brahmin Pokkharasāti. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc51
msgctxt "dn5:7.36"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo khāṇumataṃ anuppatto khāṇumate viharati ambalaṭṭhikāyaṃ. "
msgstr "The ascetic Gotama has arrived at Khāṇumata and is staying at Ambalaṭṭhikā. "

msgctxt "dn5:7.37"
msgid "Ye kho pana, bho, keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā amhākaṃ gāmakhettaṃ āgacchanti, atithī no te honti. "
msgstr "Any ascetic or brahmin who comes to stay in our village district is our guest, "

msgctxt "dn5:7.38"
msgid "Atithī kho panamhehi sakkātabbā garukātabbā mānetabbā pūjetabbā apacetabbā. "
msgstr "and should be honored and respected as such. "

msgctxt "dn5:7.39"
msgid "Yampi, bho, samaṇo gotamo khāṇumataṃ anuppatto khāṇumate viharati ambalaṭṭhikāyaṃ, atithimhākaṃ samaṇo gotamo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn5:7.40"
msgid "Atithi kho panamhehi sakkātabbo garukātabbo mānetabbo pūjetabbo apacetabbo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn5:7.41"
msgid "Imināpaṅgena nārahati so bhavaṃ gotamo amhākaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ. "
msgstr "For this reason, too, it’s not appropriate for Master Gotama to come to see me, "

msgctxt "dn5:7.42"
msgid "Atha kho mayameva arahāma taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ. "
msgstr "rather, it’s appropriate for me to go to see him. "

msgctxt "dn5:7.43"
msgid "Ettake kho ahaṃ, bho, tassa bhoto gotamassa vaṇṇe pariyāpuṇāmi, no ca kho so bhavaṃ gotamo ettakavaṇṇo. "
msgstr "This is the extent of Master Gotama’s praise that I have learned. But his praises are not confined to this, "

msgctxt "dn5:7.44"
msgid "Aparimāṇavaṇṇo hi so bhavaṃ gotamo”ti. "
msgstr "for the praise of Master Gotama is limitless.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs8, sc52
msgctxt "dn5:8.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, te brāhmaṇā kūṭadantaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, those brahmins said to him, "

msgctxt "dn5:8.2"
msgid "“yathā kho bhavaṃ kūṭadanto samaṇassa gotamassa vaṇṇe bhāsati, ito cepi so bhavaṃ gotamo yojanasate viharati, alameva saddhena kulaputtena dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ api puṭosenā”ti. "
msgstr "“According to Kūṭadanta’s praises, if Master Gotama were staying within a hundred leagues, it’d be worthwhile for a faithful gentleman to go to see him, even if they had to carry their own provisions in a shoulder bag.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:8.3"
msgid "“Tena hi, bho, sabbeva mayaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissāmā”ti. "
msgstr "“Well then, gentlemen, let’s all go to see the ascetic Gotama.” "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn5:8.4"
msgid "4. Mahāvijitarājayaññakathā "
msgstr "4. The Story of King Mahāvijita’s Sacrifice "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.134, sc53
msgctxt "dn5:8.5"
msgid "Atha kho kūṭadanto brāhmaṇo mahatā brāhmaṇagaṇena saddhiṃ yena ambalaṭṭhikā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then Kūṭadanta together with a large group of brahmins went to see the Buddha and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "dn5:8.6"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side. "

msgctxt "dn5:8.7"
msgid "Khāṇumatakāpi kho brāhmaṇagahapatikā appekacce bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce nāmagottaṃ sāvetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce tuṇhībhūtā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. "
msgstr "Before sitting down to one side, some of the brahmins and householders of Khāṇumataka bowed, some exchanged greetings and polite conversation, some held up their joined palms toward the Buddha, some announced their name and clan, while some kept silent. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs9, sc54
msgctxt "dn5:9.1"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho kūṭadanto brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Kūṭadanta said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "dn5:9.2"
msgid "“sutaṃ metaṃ, bho gotama: "
msgstr "“Master Gotama, I’ve heard that "

msgctxt "dn5:9.3"
msgid "‘samaṇo gotamo tividhaṃ yaññasampadaṃ soḷasaparikkhāraṃ jānātī’ti. "
msgstr "you know how to accomplish the sacrifice with three modes and sixteen accessories. "

msgctxt "dn5:9.4"
msgid "Na kho panāhaṃ jānāmi tividhaṃ yaññasampadaṃ soḷasaparikkhāraṃ. "
msgstr "I don’t know about that, "

msgctxt "dn5:9.5"
msgid "Icchāmi cāhaṃ mahāyaññaṃ yajituṃ. "
msgstr "but I wish to perform a great sacrifice. "

msgctxt "dn5:9.6"
msgid "Sādhu me bhavaṃ gotamo tividhaṃ yaññasampadaṃ soḷasaparikkhāraṃ desetū”ti. "
msgstr "Please teach me how to accomplish the sacrifice with three modes and sixteen accessories.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc55
msgctxt "dn5:9.7"
msgid "“Tena hi, brāhmaṇa, suṇāhi sādhukaṃ manasikarohi, bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“Well then, brahmin, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:9.8"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho kūṭadanto brāhmaṇo bhagavato paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes sir,” Kūṭadanta replied. "

msgctxt "dn5:9.9"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. REF: pts-cs10
msgctxt "dn5:10.1"
msgid "“bhūtapubbaṃ, brāhmaṇa, rājā mahāvijito nāma ahosi aḍḍho mahaddhano mahābhogo pahūtajātarūparajato pahūtavittūpakaraṇo pahūtadhanadhañño paripuṇṇakosakoṭṭhāgāro. "
msgstr "Once upon a time, brahmin, there was a king named Mahāvijita. He was rich, affluent, and wealthy, with lots of gold and silver, lots of property and assets, lots of money and grain, and a full treasury and storehouses. "

msgctxt "dn5:10.2"
msgid "Atha kho, brāhmaṇa, rañño mahāvijitassa rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi: "
msgstr "Then as King Mahāvijita was in private retreat this thought came to his mind: "

msgctxt "dn5:10.3"
msgid "‘adhigatā kho me vipulā mānusakā bhogā, mahantaṃ pathavimaṇḍalaṃ abhivijiya ajjhāvasāmi, yannūnāhaṃ mahāyaññaṃ yajeyyaṃ, yaṃ mama assa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘I have achieved human wealth, and reign after conquering this vast territory. Why don’t I hold a large sacrifice? That will be for my lasting welfare and happiness.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.135, sc56
msgctxt "dn5:10.4"
msgid "Atha kho, brāhmaṇa, rājā mahāvijito purohitaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ āmantetvā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then he summoned the brahmin high priest and said to him: "

msgctxt "dn5:10.5"
msgid "‘idha mayhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi: "
msgstr "‘Just now, brahmin, as I was in private retreat this thought came to mind, "

msgctxt "dn5:10.6"
msgid "“adhigatā kho me vipulā mānusakā bhogā, mahantaṃ pathavimaṇḍalaṃ abhivijiya ajjhāvasāmi. Yannūnāhaṃ mahāyaññaṃ yajeyyaṃ yaṃ mama assa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti. "
msgstr "“I have achieved human wealth, and reign after conquering this vast territory. Why don’t I perform a great sacrifice? That will be for my lasting welfare and happiness.” "

msgctxt "dn5:10.7"
msgid "Icchāmahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, mahāyaññaṃ yajituṃ. "
msgstr "Brahmin, I wish to perform a great sacrifice. "

msgctxt "dn5:10.8"
msgid "Anusāsatu maṃ bhavaṃ yaṃ mama assa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā’ti. "
msgstr "Please instruct me. It will be for my lasting welfare and happiness.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs11, pts-vp-pli1.136, sc57
msgctxt "dn5:11.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, brāhmaṇa, purohito brāhmaṇo rājānaṃ mahāvijitaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, the brahmin high priest said to him: "

msgctxt "dn5:11.2"
msgid "‘bhoto kho rañño janapado sakaṇṭako sauppīḷo, gāmaghātāpi dissanti, nigamaghātāpi dissanti, nagaraghātāpi dissanti, panthaduhanāpi dissanti. "
msgstr "‘Sir, the king’s realm is harried and oppressed. Bandits have been seen raiding villages, towns, and cities, and infesting the highways. "

msgctxt "dn5:11.3"
msgid "Bhavaṃ kho pana rājā evaṃ sakaṇṭake janapade sauppīḷe balimuddhareyya, akiccakārī assa tena bhavaṃ rājā. "
msgstr "But if the king were to extract more taxes while his realm is thus harried and oppressed, he would not be doing his duty. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:11.4"
msgid "Siyā kho pana bhoto rañño evamassa: "
msgstr "Now the king might think, "

msgctxt "dn5:11.5"
msgid "“ahametaṃ dassukhīlaṃ vadhena vā bandhena vā jāniyā vā garahāya vā pabbājanāya vā samūhanissāmī”ti, na kho panetassa dassukhīlassa evaṃ sammā samugghāto hoti. "
msgstr "“I’ll eradicate this barbarian obstacle by execution or imprisonment or confiscation or condemnation or banishment!” But that’s not the right way to eradicate this barbarian obstacle. "

msgctxt "dn5:11.6"
msgid "Ye te hatāvasesakā bhavissanti, te pacchā rañño janapadaṃ viheṭhessanti. "
msgstr "Those who remain after the killing will return to harass the king’s realm. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:11.7"
msgid "Api ca kho idaṃ saṃvidhānaṃ āgamma evametassa dassukhīlassa sammā samugghāto hoti. "
msgstr "Rather, here is a plan, relying on which the barbarian obstacle will be properly uprooted. "

msgctxt "dn5:11.8"
msgid "Tena hi bhavaṃ rājā ye bhoto rañño janapade ussahanti kasigorakkhe, tesaṃ bhavaṃ rājā bījabhattaṃ anuppadetu. "
msgstr "So let the king provide seed and fodder for those in the realm who work in farming and raising cattle. "

msgctxt "dn5:11.9"
msgid "Ye bhoto rañño janapade ussahanti vāṇijjāya, tesaṃ bhavaṃ rājā pābhataṃ anuppadetu. "
msgstr "Let the king provide funding for those who work in trade. "

msgctxt "dn5:11.10"
msgid "Ye bhoto rañño janapade ussahanti rājaporise, tesaṃ bhavaṃ rājā bhattavetanaṃ pakappetu. "
msgstr "Let the king guarantee food and wages for those in government service. "

msgctxt "dn5:11.11"
msgid "Te ca manussā sakammapasutā rañño janapadaṃ na viheṭhessanti; "
msgstr "Then the people, occupied with their own work, will not harass the realm. "

msgctxt "dn5:11.12"
msgid "mahā ca rañño rāsiko bhavissati. "
msgstr "The king’s revenues will be great. "

msgctxt "dn5:11.13"
msgid "Khemaṭṭhitā janapadā akaṇṭakā anuppīḷā. Manussā mudā modamānā ure putte naccentā apārutagharā maññe viharissantī’ti. "
msgstr "When the country is secured as a sanctuary, free of being harried and oppressed, the happy people, with joy in their hearts, dancing with children at their breast, will dwell as if their houses were wide open.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:11.14"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, bho’ti kho, brāhmaṇa, rājā mahāvijito purohitassa brāhmaṇassa paṭissutvā ye rañño janapade ussahiṃsu kasigorakkhe, tesaṃ rājā mahāvijito bījabhattaṃ anuppadāsi. "
msgstr "The king agreed with the high priest’s advice and followed his recommendation. "

msgctxt "dn5:11.15"
msgid "Ye ca rañño janapade ussahiṃsu vāṇijjāya, tesaṃ rājā mahāvijito pābhataṃ anuppadāsi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn5:11.16"
msgid "Ye ca rañño janapade ussahiṃsu rājaporise, tesaṃ rājā mahāvijito bhattavetanaṃ pakappesi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn5:11.17"
msgid "Te ca manussā sakammapasutā rañño janapadaṃ na viheṭhiṃsu, mahā ca rañño rāsiko ahosi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn5:11.18"
msgid "Khemaṭṭhitā janapadā akaṇṭakā anuppīḷā manussā mudā modamānā ure putte naccentā apārutagharā maññe vihariṃsu. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs12
msgctxt "dn5:12.1"
msgid "Atha kho, brāhmaṇa, rājā mahāvijito purohitaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ āmantetvā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the king summoned the brahmin high priest and said to him: "

msgctxt "dn5:12.2"
msgid "‘samūhato kho me bhoto dassukhīlo, bhoto saṃvidhānaṃ āgamma mahā ca me rāsiko. "
msgstr "‘I have eradicated the barbarian obstacle. And relying on your plan my revenue is now great. "

msgctxt "dn5:12.3"
msgid "Khemaṭṭhitā janapadā akaṇṭakā anuppīḷā manussā mudā modamānā ure putte naccentā apārutagharā maññe viharanti. "
msgstr "Since the country is secured as a sanctuary, free of being harried and oppressed, the happy people, with joy in their hearts, dancing with children at their breast, dwell as if their houses were wide open. "

msgctxt "dn5:12.4"
msgid "Icchāmahaṃ brāhmaṇa mahāyaññaṃ yajituṃ. "
msgstr "Brahmin, I wish to perform a great sacrifice. "

msgctxt "dn5:12.5"
msgid "Anusāsatu maṃ bhavaṃ yaṃ mama assa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā’ti. "
msgstr "Please instruct me. It will be for my lasting welfare and happiness.’ "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn5:12.6"
msgid "4.1. Catuparikkhāra "
msgstr "4.1. The Four Accessories "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.137, sc58
msgctxt "dn5:12.7"
msgid "Tena hi bhavaṃ rājā ye bhoto rañño janapade khattiyā ānuyantā negamā ceva jānapadā ca te bhavaṃ rājā āmantayataṃ: ‘icchāmahaṃ, bho, mahāyaññaṃ yajituṃ, anujānantu me bhavanto yaṃ mama assa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā’ti. Ye bhoto rañño janapade amaccā pārisajjā negamā ceva jānapadā ca … pe … brāhmaṇamahāsālā negamā ceva jānapadā ca … pe … gahapatinecayikā negamā ceva jānapadā ca, te bhavaṃ rājā āmantayataṃ: "
msgstr "‘In that case, let the king announce this throughout the realm to the aristocrat vassals, ministers and counselors, well-to-do brahmins, and well-off householders, both of town and country: "

msgctxt "dn5:12.8"
msgid "‘icchāmahaṃ, bho, mahāyaññaṃ yajituṃ, anujānantu me bhavanto yaṃ mama assa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā’ti. "
msgstr "“I wish to perform a great sacrifice. Please grant your approval, gentlemen; it will be for my lasting welfare and happiness.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:12.9"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, bho’ti kho, brāhmaṇa, rājā mahāvijito purohitassa brāhmaṇassa paṭissutvā ye rañño janapade khattiyā ānuyantā negamā ceva jānapadā ca, te rājā mahāvijito āmantesi: "
msgstr "The king agreed with the high priest’s advice and followed his recommendation. "

msgctxt "dn5:12.10"
msgid "‘icchāmahaṃ, bho, mahāyaññaṃ yajituṃ, anujānantu me bhavanto yaṃ mama assa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā’ti. "
msgstr "And all of the people who were thus informed responded by saying: "

msgctxt "dn5:12.11"
msgid "‘Yajataṃ bhavaṃ rājā yaññaṃ, yaññakālo, mahārājā’ti. "
msgstr "‘May the king perform a sacrifice! It is time for a sacrifice, great king.’ "

msgctxt "dn5:12.12"
msgid "Ye rañño janapade amaccā pārisajjā negamā ceva jānapadā ca … pe … brāhmaṇamahāsālā negamā ceva jānapadā ca … pe … gahapatinecayikā negamā ceva jānapadā ca, te rājā mahāvijito āmantesi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn5:12.13"
msgid "‘icchāmahaṃ, bho, mahāyaññaṃ yajituṃ. Anujānantu me bhavanto yaṃ mama assa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn5:12.14"
msgid "‘Yajataṃ bhavaṃ rājā yaññaṃ, yaññakālo, mahārājā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn5:12.15"
msgid "Itime cattāro anumatipakkhā tasseva yaññassa parikkhārā bhavanti. "
msgstr "And so these four consenting factions became accessories to the sacrifice. "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn5:12.16"
msgid "4.2. Aṭṭhaparikkhāra "
msgstr "4.2. The Eight Accessories "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs13, sc59
msgctxt "dn5:13.1"
msgid "Rājā mahāvijito aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgato—"
msgstr "King Mahāvijita possessed eight factors. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:13.2"
msgid "ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena; "
msgstr "He was well born on both his mother’s and father’s side, of pure descent, irrefutable and impeccable in questions of ancestry back to the seventh paternal generation. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:13.3"
msgid "abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgato brahmavaṇṇī brahmavacchasī akhuddāvakāso dassanāya; "
msgstr "He was attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty. He was magnificent, splendid, remarkable to behold. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:13.4"
msgid "aḍḍho mahaddhano mahābhogo pahūtajātarūparajato pahūtavittūpakaraṇo pahūtadhanadhañño paripuṇṇakosakoṭṭhāgāro; "
msgstr "He was rich, affluent, and wealthy, with lots of gold and silver, lots of property and assets, lots of money and grain, and a full treasury and storehouses. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: Here sahati is the preferred reading, against PTS, RD, MW. This sounds rather like Alexander arriving in India.
#. VAR: sahati → patapati (bj, pts1) | tapati (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn5:13.5"
msgid "balavā caturaṅginiyā senāya samannāgato assavāya ovādapaṭikarāya sahati maññe paccatthike yasasā; "
msgstr "He was powerful, having an army of four divisions that was obedient and carried out instructions. He’d probably prevail over his enemies just with his reputation. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: For this long compound, see SN 2.23
msgctxt "dn5:13.6"
msgid "saddho dāyako dānapati anāvaṭadvāro samaṇabrāhmaṇakapaṇaddhikavaṇibbakayācakānaṃ opānabhūto puññāni karoti; "
msgstr "He was faithful, generous, a donor, his door always open. He was a well-spring of support, making merit with ascetics and brahmins, for paupers, vagrants, travelers, and beggars. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:13.7"
msgid "bahussuto tassa tassa sutajātassa, tassa tasseva kho pana bhāsitassa atthaṃ jānāti: "
msgstr "He was very learned in diverse fields of learning. He understood the meaning of diverse statements, saying: "

msgctxt "dn5:13.8"
msgid "‘ayaṃ imassa bhāsitassa attho ayaṃ imassa bhāsitassa attho’ti; "
msgstr "‘This is what that statement means; that is what this statement means.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:13.9"
msgid "paṇḍito, viyatto, medhāvī, paṭibalo, atītānāgatapaccuppanne atthe cintetuṃ. "
msgstr "He was astute, competent, and intelligent, able to think issues through as they bear upon the past, future, and present. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:13.10"
msgid "Rājā mahāvijito imehi aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgato. "
msgstr "These are the eight factors that King Mahāvijita possessed. "

msgctxt "dn5:13.11"
msgid "Iti imānipi aṭṭhaṅgāni tasseva yaññassa parikkhārā bhavanti. "
msgstr "And so these eight factors also became accessories to the sacrifice. "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn5:13.12"
msgid "4.3. Catuparikkhāra "
msgstr "4.3. Four More Accessories "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs14, pts-vp-pli1.138, sc60
#. VAR: Purohito → purohitopi (bj, km, c1)
msgctxt "dn5:14.1"
msgid "Purohito brāhmaṇo catūhaṅgehi samannāgato, "
msgstr "And the brahmin high priest had four factors. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:14.2"
msgid "ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena; "
msgstr "He was well born on both his mother’s and father’s side, of pure descent, irrefutable and impeccable in questions of ancestry back to the seventh paternal generation. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:14.3"
msgid "ajjhāyako mantadharo tiṇṇaṃ vedānaṃ pāragū sanighaṇḍukeṭubhānaṃ sākkharappabhedānaṃ itihāsapañcamānaṃ padako veyyākaraṇo lokāyatamahāpurisalakkhaṇesu anavayo; "
msgstr "He recited and remembered the hymns, and had mastered the three Vedas, together with their vocabularies, ritual, phonology and etymology, and the testament as fifth. He knew philology and grammar, and was well versed in cosmology and the marks of a great man. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:14.4"
msgid "sīlavā vuddhasīlī vuddhasīlena samannāgato; "
msgstr "He was ethical, mature in ethical conduct. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:14.5"
msgid "paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī paṭhamo vā dutiyo vā sujaṃ paggaṇhantānaṃ. "
msgstr "He was astute and clever, being the first or second to hold the sacrificial ladle. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:14.6"
msgid "Purohito brāhmaṇo imehi catūhaṅgehi samannāgato. "
msgstr "These are the four factors that the brahmin high priest possessed. "

#. VAR: imānipi → imāni (c1)
msgctxt "dn5:14.7"
msgid "Iti imānipi cattāri aṅgāni tasseva yaññassa parikkhārā bhavanti. "
msgstr "And so these four factors also became accessories to the sacrifice. "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn5:14.8"
msgid "4.4. Tissovidhā "
msgstr "4.4. The Three Modes "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs15, sc61
msgctxt "dn5:15.1"
msgid "Atha kho, brāhmaṇa, purohito brāhmaṇo rañño mahāvijitassa pubbeva yaññā tisso vidhā desesi. "
msgstr "Next, before the sacrifice, the brahmin high priest taught the three modes to the king. "

#. VAR: yiṭṭhukāmassa → yajamānassa (s1-3) | yiṭṭhakāmassa (mr)
msgctxt "dn5:15.2"
msgid "Siyā kho pana bhoto rañño mahāyaññaṃ yiṭṭhukāmassa kocideva vippaṭisāro: "
msgstr "‘Now, though the king wants to perform a great sacrifice, he might have certain regrets, thinking: "

msgctxt "dn5:15.3"
msgid "‘“mahā vata me bhogakkhandho vigacchissatī”ti, so bhotā raññā vippaṭisāro na karaṇīyo. "
msgstr "“I shall lose a great fortune,” or "

msgctxt "dn5:15.4"
msgid "Siyā kho pana bhoto rañño mahāyaññaṃ yajamānassa kocideva vippaṭisāro: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn5:15.5"
msgid "“mahā vata me bhogakkhandho vigacchatī”ti, so bhotā raññā vippaṭisāro na karaṇīyo. "
msgstr "“I am losing a great fortune,” or "

msgctxt "dn5:15.6"
msgid "Siyā kho pana bhoto rañño mahāyaññaṃ yiṭṭhassa kocideva vippaṭisāro: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn5:15.7"
msgid "“mahā vata me bhogakkhandho vigato”ti, so bhotā raññā vippaṭisāro na karaṇīyo’ti. "
msgstr "“I have lost a great fortune.” But the king should not harbor such regrets.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:15.8"
msgid "Imā kho, brāhmaṇa, purohito brāhmaṇo rañño mahāvijitassa pubbeva yaññā tisso vidhā desesi. "
msgstr "These are the three modes that the brahmin high priest taught to the king before the sacrifice. "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn5:15.9"
msgid "4.5. Dasaākāra "
msgstr "4.5. The Ten Respects "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs16, pts-vp-pli1.139, sc62
msgctxt "dn5:16.1"
msgid "Atha kho, brāhmaṇa, purohito brāhmaṇo rañño mahāvijitassa pubbeva yaññā dasahākārehi paṭiggāhakesu vippaṭisāraṃ paṭivinesi. "
msgstr "Next, before the sacrifice, the brahmin high priest dispelled the king’s regret regarding the recipients in ten respects: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:16.2"
msgid "‘Āgamissanti kho bhoto yaññaṃ pāṇātipātinopi pāṇātipātā paṭiviratāpi. "
msgstr "‘There will come to the sacrifice those who kill living creatures and those who refrain from killing living creatures. "

msgctxt "dn5:16.3"
msgid "Ye tattha pāṇātipātino, tesaññeva tena. "
msgstr "As to those who kill living creatures, the outcome of that is theirs alone. "

# NOTE: PTS, followed by RD and MW, acknowledges sajjata only as vl, but it is in comm, so should be accepted.
msgctxt "dn5:16.4"
msgid "Ye tattha pāṇātipātā paṭiviratā, te ārabbha yajataṃ bhavaṃ, sajjataṃ bhavaṃ, modataṃ bhavaṃ, cittameva bhavaṃ antaraṃ pasādetu. "
msgstr "But as to those who refrain from killing living creatures, it is for their sakes that the king should sacrifice, relinquish, rejoice, and gain confidence in his heart. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:16.5"
msgid "Āgamissanti kho bhoto yaññaṃ adinnādāyinopi adinnādānā paṭiviratāpi … pe … "
msgstr "There will come to the sacrifice those who steal … "

msgctxt "dn5:16.6"
msgid "kāmesu micchācārinopi kāmesumicchācārā paṭiviratāpi … "
msgstr "commit sexual misconduct … "

msgctxt "dn5:16.7"
msgid "musāvādinopi musāvādā paṭiviratāpi … "
msgstr "lie … "

msgctxt "dn5:16.8"
msgid "pisuṇavācinopi pisuṇāya vācāya paṭiviratāpi … "
msgstr "use divisive speech … "

msgctxt "dn5:16.9"
msgid "pharusavācinopi pharusāya vācāya paṭiviratāpi … "
msgstr "use harsh speech … "

msgctxt "dn5:16.10"
msgid "samphappalāpinopi samphappalāpā paṭiviratāpi … "
msgstr "talk nonsense … "

msgctxt "dn5:16.11"
msgid "abhijjhālunopi anabhijjhālunopi … "
msgstr "are covetous … "

msgctxt "dn5:16.12"
msgid "byāpannacittāpi abyāpannacittāpi … "
msgstr "have ill will … "

msgctxt "dn5:16.13"
msgid "micchādiṭṭhikāpi sammādiṭṭhikāpi …. "
msgstr "have wrong view and those who have right view. "

msgctxt "dn5:16.14"
msgid "Ye tattha micchādiṭṭhikā, tesaññeva tena. "
msgstr "As to those who have wrong view, the outcome of that is theirs alone. "

msgctxt "dn5:16.15"
msgid "Ye tattha sammādiṭṭhikā, te ārabbha yajataṃ bhavaṃ, sajjataṃ bhavaṃ, modataṃ bhavaṃ, cittameva bhavaṃ antaraṃ pasādetū’ti. "
msgstr "But as to those who have right view, it is for their sakes that the king should sacrifice, relinquish, rejoice, and gain confidence in his heart.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:16.16"
msgid "Imehi kho, brāhmaṇa, purohito brāhmaṇo rañño mahāvijitassa pubbeva yaññā dasahākārehi paṭiggāhakesu vippaṭisāraṃ paṭivinesi. "
msgstr "These are the ten respects in which the high priest dispelled the king’s regret regarding the recipients before the sacrifice. "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn5:16.17"
msgid "4.6. Soḷasākāra "
msgstr "4.6. The Sixteen Respects "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs17
msgctxt "dn5:17.1"
msgid "Atha kho, brāhmaṇa, purohito brāhmaṇo rañño mahāvijitassa mahāyaññaṃ yajamānassa soḷasahākārehi cittaṃ sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi "
msgstr "Next, while the king was performing the great sacrifice, the brahmin high priest educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired the king’s mind in sixteen respects: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn5:17.2"
msgid "siyā kho pana bhoto rañño mahāyaññaṃ yajamānassa kocideva vattā: "
msgstr "‘Now, while the king is performing the great sacrifice, someone might say, "

msgctxt "dn5:17.3"
msgid "‘rājā kho mahāvijito mahāyaññaṃ yajati, no ca kho tassa āmantitā khattiyā ānuyantā negamā ceva jānapadā ca; "
msgstr "“King Mahāvijita performs a great sacrifice, but he did not announce it to the aristocrat vassals of town and country. "

msgctxt "dn5:17.4"
msgid "atha ca pana bhavaṃ rājā evarūpaṃ mahāyaññaṃ yajatī’ti. "
msgstr "That’s the kind of great sacrifice that this king performs.” "

msgctxt "dn5:17.5"
msgid "Evampi bhoto rañño vattā dhammato natthi. "
msgstr "Those who speak against the king in this way have no legitimacy. "

msgctxt "dn5:17.6"
msgid "Bhotā kho pana raññā āmantitā khattiyā ānuyantā negamā ceva jānapadā ca. "
msgstr "For the king did indeed announce it to the aristocrat vassals of town and country. "

msgctxt "dn5:17.7"
msgid "Imināpetaṃ bhavaṃ rājā jānātu, yajataṃ bhavaṃ, sajjataṃ bhavaṃ, modataṃ bhavaṃ, cittameva bhavaṃ antaraṃ pasādetu. (1) "
msgstr "Let the king know this as a reason to sacrifice, relinquish, rejoice, and gain confidence in his heart. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc64
msgctxt "dn5:17.8"
msgid "Siyā kho pana bhoto rañño mahāyaññaṃ yajamānassa kocideva vattā: "
msgstr "While the king is performing the great sacrifice, someone might say, "

msgctxt "dn5:17.9"
msgid "‘rājā kho mahāvijito mahāyaññaṃ yajati, no ca kho tassa āmantitā amaccā pārisajjā negamā ceva jānapadā ca … pe … brāhmaṇamahāsālā negamā ceva jānapadā ca … pe … gahapatinecayikā negamā ceva jānapadā ca, atha ca pana bhavaṃ rājā evarūpaṃ mahāyaññaṃ yajatī’ti. "
msgstr "“King Mahāvijita performs a great sacrifice, but he did not announce it to the ministers and counselors, well-to-do brahmins, and well-off householders, both of town and country. That’s the kind of great sacrifice that this king performs.” "

msgctxt "dn5:17.10"
msgid "Evampi bhoto rañño vattā dhammato natthi. "
msgstr "Those who speak against the king in this way have no legitimacy. "

msgctxt "dn5:17.11"
msgid "Bhotā kho pana raññā āmantitā gahapatinecayikā negamā ceva jānapadā ca. "
msgstr "For the king did indeed announce it to all these people. "

msgctxt "dn5:17.12"
msgid "Imināpetaṃ bhavaṃ rājā jānātu, yajataṃ bhavaṃ, sajjataṃ bhavaṃ, modataṃ bhavaṃ, cittameva bhavaṃ antaraṃ pasādetu. (2–4.) "
msgstr "Let the king know this too as a reason to sacrifice, relinquish, rejoice, and gain confidence in his heart. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.140, sc65
msgctxt "dn5:17.13"
msgid "Siyā kho pana bhoto rañño mahāyaññaṃ yajamānassa kocideva vattā: "
msgstr "While the king is performing the great sacrifice, someone might say "

msgctxt "dn5:17.14"
msgid "‘rājā kho mahāvijito mahāyaññaṃ yajati, no ca kho ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena, atha ca pana bhavaṃ rājā evarūpaṃ mahāyaññaṃ yajatī’ti. "
msgstr "that he does not possess the eight factors. "

msgctxt "dn5:17.15"
msgid "Evampi bhoto rañño vattā dhammato natthi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn5:17.16"
msgid "Bhavaṃ kho pana rājā ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn5:17.17"
msgid "Imināpetaṃ bhavaṃ rājā jānātu, yajataṃ bhavaṃ, sajjataṃ bhavaṃ, modataṃ bhavaṃ, cittameva bhavaṃ antaraṃ pasādetu. (5) "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc66
msgctxt "dn5:17.18"
msgid "Siyā kho pana bhoto rañño mahāyaññaṃ yajamānassa kocideva vattā: "
